WEBVTT

00:00:11.011 --> 00:00:15.015
NOTES FROM THE LAST ROW

00:00:20.311 --> 00:00:22.313
Here.

00:00:27.318 --> 00:00:29.779
Hurry! That woman is... How awful.

00:00:34.117 --> 00:00:35.618
Mr. Heo, let's go.

00:00:37.162 --> 00:00:40.081
You know it'd be bad if Mr. Kim saw me here.

00:01:09.986 --> 00:01:11.029
I'm sorry.

00:01:12.989 --> 00:01:14.032
I never imagined...

00:01:15.992 --> 00:01:17.118
I just wanted

00:01:17.786 --> 00:01:20.914
To prove to you what I saw.

00:01:28.171 --> 00:01:29.506
Please drop me off here.

00:01:30.340 --> 00:01:31.925
I'll walk the rest.

00:01:44.479 --> 00:01:46.272
Thank you for the ride.

00:01:47.315 --> 00:01:48.650
See you in tomorrow's class.

00:01:56.950 --> 00:02:00.078
Tell me the truth, and don't you dare think about lying.

00:02:02.288 --> 00:02:05.542
Did you really not know, or did you just pretend not to?

00:02:06.626 --> 00:02:07.460
Sorry?

00:02:08.253 --> 00:02:09.129
What do you mean?

00:02:09.629 --> 00:02:12.298
Why didn't you tell me who Se-yun's dad is?

00:02:13.800 --> 00:02:15.593
Don't tell me you didn't know.

00:02:18.221 --> 00:02:19.347
What do you...

00:02:20.098 --> 00:02:21.391
Who is Mr. Kim?

00:02:23.977 --> 00:02:25.562
Don't know Kim Su-hun, the author?

00:03:00.763 --> 00:03:02.307
<i>Kim Su-hun, the author?</i>

00:03:03.892 --> 00:03:05.393
Kim Su-hun, the author...

00:03:07.187 --> 00:03:09.354
So Se-yun's dad is an author.

00:03:09.355 --> 00:03:10.607
No wonder.

00:03:12.358 --> 00:03:14.694
I'm not too familiar with many authors.

00:03:17.197 --> 00:03:18.281
So what?

00:03:19.365 --> 00:03:20.992
So what if he's Kim Su-hun?

00:03:22.535 --> 00:03:24.120
Is that important right now?

00:04:01.032 --> 00:04:03.952
So it was you all along, Kim Su-hun.

00:04:24.264 --> 00:04:25.473
Mom.

00:04:39.779 --> 00:04:42.240
Right, it's you.

00:05:05.847 --> 00:05:06.931
Mun-oh?

00:05:08.391 --> 00:05:10.560
You skipped class too?

00:05:22.447 --> 00:05:23.281
Oh, here.

00:05:24.907 --> 00:05:25.950
What's this?

00:05:28.161 --> 00:05:31.247
I adore this poet. How did you know?

00:05:32.081 --> 00:05:33.624
Oh my gosh.

00:05:36.544 --> 00:05:38.962
Thank you so much for this, Mun-oh.

00:05:38.963 --> 00:05:41.090
I'll see you later.

00:05:44.218 --> 00:05:46.054
- Eun-joo. - Su-hun!

00:05:46.804 --> 00:05:47.764
Well, well.

00:05:48.806 --> 00:05:50.975
What a surprise. Where are you headed?

00:06:03.696 --> 00:06:05.615
Please don't think too much.

00:06:06.657 --> 00:06:09.660
The most important thing to me is that you feel at peace.

00:06:10.370 --> 00:06:13.081
In our family, nothing matters more than that.

00:07:13.891 --> 00:07:15.852
Kim Su-hun, you son of a bitch.

00:07:18.187 --> 00:07:20.189
How could you betray dear Eun-joo...

00:07:37.039 --> 00:07:43.378
We don't call everything that happens in our daily lives an incident, do we?

00:07:43.379 --> 00:07:44.964
Regardless of size,

00:07:45.590 --> 00:07:48.551
If an event has a significant impact

00:07:49.552 --> 00:07:52.388
On the lives and actions of the characters,

00:07:53.181 --> 00:07:57.268
Then we can call it a narrative incident.

00:08:00.271 --> 00:08:02.440
And such events...

00:08:09.780 --> 00:08:10.907
Always stem from...

00:08:13.576 --> 00:08:15.328
The intricate conflicts

00:08:16.370 --> 00:08:17.497
Within the human mind...

00:08:26.088 --> 00:08:27.006
I'm sorry.

00:08:27.757 --> 00:08:29.258
So these conflicts...

00:08:30.218 --> 00:08:32.345
Hold on. Where was I?

00:08:42.647 --> 00:08:44.065
My office, now.

00:08:54.033 --> 00:08:55.409
You punk.

00:08:57.328 --> 00:08:59.455
Why do you always sit

00:09:00.081 --> 00:09:02.833
In the last row of the lecture hall?

00:09:04.210 --> 00:09:05.545
It's so you can daydream

00:09:06.921 --> 00:09:08.965
Instead of paying attention, isn't it?

00:09:11.300 --> 00:09:13.302
You can see everything from there.

00:09:14.845 --> 00:09:18.599
A seat where I can observe everything without being seen myself.

00:09:25.147 --> 00:09:25.982
Listen.

00:09:29.193 --> 00:09:30.778
About what happened last night.

00:09:31.779 --> 00:09:33.114
Tell me more about it.

00:09:33.990 --> 00:09:36.408
What was her name again? Min-hui?

00:09:36.409 --> 00:09:40.246
Seon Min-hui, was it? The woman who got into that accident.

00:09:41.330 --> 00:09:42.415
And

00:09:43.374 --> 00:09:44.208
Kim Su...

00:09:45.334 --> 00:09:46.586
Se-yun's dad.

00:09:48.129 --> 00:09:49.755
What's he been doing since then?

00:09:51.007 --> 00:09:51.841
Tell me.

00:09:55.136 --> 00:09:55.970
What?

00:09:58.556 --> 00:09:59.473
You don't want to?

00:10:02.935 --> 00:10:05.605
You should at least tell <i>me</i>.

00:10:06.188 --> 00:10:09.357
I was also there last night, thanks to you.

00:10:09.358 --> 00:10:10.401
She's dead.

00:10:16.198 --> 00:10:17.241
Dead?

00:10:18.284 --> 00:10:19.327
The police called

00:10:19.952 --> 00:10:21.370
This morning.

00:10:31.839 --> 00:10:32.923
So, in the end...

00:10:37.261 --> 00:10:38.179
In the end...

00:10:40.056 --> 00:10:41.140
So, in the end...

00:10:45.269 --> 00:10:47.772
Mr. Heo, do you know Kim Su-hun personally?

00:10:48.272 --> 00:10:49.565
How well do you know him?

00:10:53.194 --> 00:10:54.028
What?

00:10:55.363 --> 00:10:56.739
I don't know him that well.

00:10:57.490 --> 00:11:00.534
I just know he's a famous author, that's all.

00:11:01.035 --> 00:11:02.411
Why are you lying?

00:11:06.123 --> 00:11:06.957
What did you say?

00:11:08.959 --> 00:11:10.711
I heard you two are friends.

00:11:11.212 --> 00:11:15.132
Se-yun told me that you hosted the special lecture

00:11:15.716 --> 00:11:17.051
He gave at school recently.

00:11:19.095 --> 00:11:19.929
Look.

00:11:20.846 --> 00:11:24.058
Do you think only friends can host a discussion?

00:11:25.476 --> 00:11:27.228
We just went to college together.

00:11:29.980 --> 00:11:32.191
I don't know him that well. Wait.

00:11:33.693 --> 00:11:34.694
Why do you ask?

00:11:36.946 --> 00:11:38.072
Well, Mr. Kim...

00:11:44.161 --> 00:11:45.287
What about Kim Su-hun?

00:11:48.541 --> 00:11:50.376
I just wonder what kind of person he is.

00:11:51.252 --> 00:11:53.629
I liked him at first, but now he seems strange.

00:11:54.714 --> 00:11:57.758
He's way too calm, considering what happened last night.

00:11:58.467 --> 00:12:01.512
That's not the only strange thing. I wrote it down here, so...

00:12:05.224 --> 00:12:06.934
- You wrote it already? - Oh, but...

00:12:10.312 --> 00:12:11.522
It's my last assignment.

00:12:13.983 --> 00:12:15.443
You said so yesterday.

00:12:16.318 --> 00:12:17.903
That our lessons are over now.

00:12:18.738 --> 00:12:20.239
And now, with what happened...

00:12:28.289 --> 00:12:29.999
I have my convenience store gig now.

00:12:35.796 --> 00:12:37.298
Thank you,

00:12:38.758 --> 00:12:40.509
And sorry about everything, Mr. Heo.

00:12:41.010 --> 00:12:42.136
That's not...

00:12:44.513 --> 00:12:45.806
Hey, I...

00:13:17.421 --> 00:13:20.633
<i>When the line between beauty and ugliness gets blurred,</i>

00:13:21.133 --> 00:13:23.677
<i>everything becomes a question mark.</i>

00:13:26.180 --> 00:13:29.140
<i>That's what the world was like this morning.</i>

00:13:29.141 --> 00:13:31.393
She didn't come to work yesterday either?

00:13:33.479 --> 00:13:34.772
And without notice?

00:13:37.399 --> 00:13:39.026
Oh my, I had no idea.

00:13:39.652 --> 00:13:42.362
I called her at least three times yesterday,

00:13:42.363 --> 00:13:43.948
But she didn't pick up.

00:13:45.115 --> 00:13:48.118
She's just being petty because I gave her a stern talking-to.

00:13:48.619 --> 00:13:50.162
What an awful attitude.

00:13:50.663 --> 00:13:53.082
After I went out of my way to talk to her that day.

00:13:53.999 --> 00:13:58.003
I think generosity and compassion are wasted on people like her.

00:13:59.046 --> 00:14:01.005
I'm not letting this slide anymore.

00:14:01.006 --> 00:14:02.633
Yeah, let her quit.

00:14:03.717 --> 00:14:07.388
Didn't I tell you before not to stress yourself out over her?

00:14:07.888 --> 00:14:09.849
I'll tell her when she comes tomorrow.

00:14:10.349 --> 00:14:13.769
You don't think she'll be a no-show tomorrow too, do you?

00:14:15.479 --> 00:14:16.313
What you doing?

00:14:17.523 --> 00:14:18.899
It's nothing.

00:14:22.987 --> 00:14:24.989
Hey. Are you all ready to go?

00:14:26.031 --> 00:14:29.034
Just wait a bit. I'm almost done setting the table.

00:14:30.244 --> 00:14:34.247
No complaining about side dishes today. Especially you, Kim Se-yun.

00:14:34.248 --> 00:14:36.417
Just say "it's good," and eat.

00:14:37.710 --> 00:14:38.835
What's going on?

00:14:38.836 --> 00:14:40.671
Don't worry about it.

00:14:42.047 --> 00:14:44.717
I'll be making the side dishes for the time being.

00:14:46.510 --> 00:14:49.346
Or we can buy them until we hire someone new.

00:14:50.097 --> 00:14:52.308
Wait, Min-hui's quitting?

00:14:52.808 --> 00:14:54.267
Why? When did she quit?

00:14:54.268 --> 00:14:57.061
She must be sulking. Your mom told her off.

00:14:57.062 --> 00:14:59.106
She's gone radio silent since yesterday.

00:15:01.609 --> 00:15:04.361
Why, honey? Are you sad to hear she's quitting?

00:15:05.571 --> 00:15:08.032
No, it's not like that. Don't worry about it.

00:15:11.327 --> 00:15:14.955
No, Kang. You should just eat up. You'll be late for school.

00:15:17.374 --> 00:15:18.208
Kang, sit.

00:15:22.588 --> 00:15:24.173
Yes, hello?

00:15:25.424 --> 00:15:26.258
Excuse me?

00:15:28.260 --> 00:15:29.094
The police?

00:15:32.973 --> 00:15:33.807
What?

00:15:35.225 --> 00:15:36.685
What do you mean...

00:15:44.652 --> 00:15:45.903
Oh my God.

00:15:49.031 --> 00:15:51.533
- Honey, this is terrible. - What's going on?

00:15:53.118 --> 00:15:53.953
Honey.

00:15:54.578 --> 00:15:57.665
It's Min-hui. Yesterday, she... I mean,

00:15:58.290 --> 00:15:59.625
Early this morning...

00:16:00.125 --> 00:16:01.125
Min-hui?

00:16:01.126 --> 00:16:02.336
What about her?

00:16:04.713 --> 00:16:05.673
Hello?

00:16:06.173 --> 00:16:07.549
Yes, what's this about?

00:16:08.759 --> 00:16:10.511
Yes, you can tell me.

00:16:17.518 --> 00:16:18.686
What is it, Mrs. Ahn?

00:16:19.520 --> 00:16:21.063
What about Min-hui...

00:16:24.441 --> 00:16:26.151
She died in a car accident?

00:16:26.694 --> 00:16:27.820
In the ER?

00:16:31.615 --> 00:16:33.784
What do you mean "no family"? That's impossible.

00:16:36.245 --> 00:16:37.328
Well, honestly,

00:16:37.329 --> 00:16:39.915
We don't really know much about her family either...

00:16:43.377 --> 00:16:45.211
Yun! What...

00:16:45.212 --> 00:16:46.337
What's wrong?

00:16:46.338 --> 00:16:48.089
- Yes, let me know. - What's wrong?

00:16:48.090 --> 00:16:50.426
- Yes. - What's wrong?

00:16:50.926 --> 00:16:53.636
- Not the home phone. Call my cell. - Yun, what's wrong?

00:16:53.637 --> 00:16:55.763
- Yun. - My cell phone number is...

00:16:55.764 --> 00:16:58.183
- Easy. Can you lift his head? - My number's 010...

00:16:59.435 --> 00:17:01.936
- 248, then 5117. - Yun?

00:17:01.937 --> 00:17:03.105
- Yes, thanks. - Yun?

00:17:03.689 --> 00:17:07.609
Focus on my voice. Yun, just keep breathing, will you?

00:17:12.823 --> 00:17:15.784
Do what we learned at the hospital. Breathe. There you go.

00:17:16.368 --> 00:17:17.703
Keep rubbing his hand.

00:17:32.092 --> 00:17:33.510
Do you think he'll be okay?

00:17:34.178 --> 00:17:36.262
Maybe we should get him to a doctor?

00:17:36.263 --> 00:17:39.850
He's just in shock. There's no need to see a doctor for that.

00:17:40.350 --> 00:17:44.063
He took a sedative, so he'll be fine after he sleeps it off.

00:17:45.355 --> 00:17:47.524
Let's go. We should let him sleep.

00:17:55.032 --> 00:17:57.785
His problem is that he's too weak-hearted.

00:17:59.286 --> 00:18:02.956
I thought playing sports would help, but he hasn't changed a bit.

00:18:03.457 --> 00:18:04.750
Are you okay?

00:18:07.252 --> 00:18:08.462
No.

00:18:08.962 --> 00:18:10.881
If I'm honest, I'm heartbroken too.

00:18:12.424 --> 00:18:15.427
I can't stop thinking about how mean I was to Min-hui.

00:18:18.472 --> 00:18:20.307
That day, I shouldn't have let her

00:18:20.933 --> 00:18:22.643
Walk away like that.

00:18:27.731 --> 00:18:30.526
You're overthinking again.

00:18:31.110 --> 00:18:33.153
You didn't do anything wrong.

00:18:34.738 --> 00:18:35.906
It's okay.

00:18:36.949 --> 00:18:39.450
Our lives are in the hands of fate. It's a shame, but...

00:18:39.451 --> 00:18:43.455
<i>When the line between kindness and cruelty gets blurred,</i>

00:18:44.540 --> 00:18:46.458
<i>everything becomes a question mark.</i>

00:18:59.471 --> 00:19:03.517
<i>Like that smile that harbors some unknown malice.</i>

00:19:16.113 --> 00:19:17.156
"Malice"?

00:19:20.284 --> 00:19:21.201
Malice.

00:19:27.833 --> 00:19:28.834
Malice...

00:19:32.004 --> 00:19:34.006
Malice? What does he mean by that?

00:19:45.976 --> 00:19:47.019
Have a good one.

00:20:05.704 --> 00:20:06.538
Welcome...

00:20:08.582 --> 00:20:09.541
Mr. Heo?

00:20:15.380 --> 00:20:17.299
A pack of these.

00:20:19.509 --> 00:20:21.094
How did you know I worked here?

00:20:21.845 --> 00:20:25.390
You told me that you worked at the convenience store by the intersection.

00:20:28.977 --> 00:20:30.394
Did you come here to see me?

00:20:30.395 --> 00:20:32.731
I was on my way home and out of cigarettes.

00:20:35.776 --> 00:20:37.151
Why are you grinning?

00:20:37.152 --> 00:20:38.070
They're obvious.

00:20:39.279 --> 00:20:40.155
Your lies.

00:20:43.283 --> 00:20:44.618
What do you want to say?

00:20:46.203 --> 00:20:47.246
That's why you're here.

00:20:50.123 --> 00:20:52.334
If you're not too busy, let's talk.

00:20:58.048 --> 00:20:59.174
You know...

00:21:01.343 --> 00:21:04.846
I only said we should stop our lessons...

00:21:07.641 --> 00:21:10.894
Because I got mad.

00:21:14.898 --> 00:21:15.857
What about you?

00:21:16.858 --> 00:21:19.945
Don't you think you'd regret it if we just end them like this?

00:21:23.448 --> 00:21:24.408
I would

00:21:25.117 --> 00:21:26.660
Love to continue, of course.

00:21:27.661 --> 00:21:29.204
And I want to keep writing.

00:21:32.416 --> 00:21:34.250
I just wonder if you'd be all right.

00:21:34.251 --> 00:21:35.168
About Mr. Kim...

00:21:37.004 --> 00:21:40.215
Since you know him personally, this must be awkward.

00:21:42.050 --> 00:21:43.051
That's true.

00:21:45.595 --> 00:21:48.432
Ethically speaking, I am conflicted about it.

00:21:49.933 --> 00:21:51.601
Even if we're not close,

00:21:52.853 --> 00:21:55.355
He's not a complete stranger either.

00:21:56.606 --> 00:21:59.651
But, for the sake of your studies,

00:22:00.152 --> 00:22:02.696
I think it'd only be my duty as a teacher

00:22:03.405 --> 00:22:06.658
To continue the lessons as originally planned.

00:22:08.160 --> 00:22:09.161
Besides,

00:22:10.787 --> 00:22:12.247
I think it's only right...

00:22:14.708 --> 00:22:16.418
For me to be braver

00:22:16.918 --> 00:22:18.086
At times like these.

00:22:20.839 --> 00:22:22.841
As long as you're okay with it...

00:22:26.636 --> 00:22:27.679
Thank you.

00:22:28.180 --> 00:22:29.722
Thank you.

00:22:29.723 --> 00:22:31.307
Frankly speaking,

00:22:31.308 --> 00:22:34.353
It doesn't really matter to me who Mr. Kim is.

00:22:35.729 --> 00:22:38.440
What I'm learning from you is far more important.

00:22:42.944 --> 00:22:44.988
Now that's what I like to hear.

00:22:45.489 --> 00:22:47.032
That's the attitude.

00:22:49.993 --> 00:22:52.454
We just need to continue our lessons

00:22:53.080 --> 00:22:54.998
With that very mindset, okay?

00:23:00.045 --> 00:23:01.171
But

00:23:01.922 --> 00:23:03.131
There's no need

00:23:03.715 --> 00:23:06.301
To tell Kim Su-hun about me.

00:23:07.677 --> 00:23:08.845
You understand, right?

00:23:09.346 --> 00:23:12.098
The minute you do, you can say goodbye to our lessons.

00:23:12.099 --> 00:23:13.432
I know, Mr. Heo.

00:23:13.433 --> 00:23:14.893
I know that much.

00:23:15.894 --> 00:23:17.521
I don't want to tell him either.

00:23:18.021 --> 00:23:20.022
I don't even want to talk to Mr. Kim anymore.

00:23:20.023 --> 00:23:21.400
You've read what I wrote.

00:23:35.914 --> 00:23:39.459
Speaking of your assignment,

00:23:39.960 --> 00:23:42.253
What did you mean by that last bit?

00:23:42.254 --> 00:23:43.171
"Malice"?

00:23:45.215 --> 00:23:46.049
How would I know?

00:23:47.676 --> 00:23:50.053
I just wrote what I saw and felt in the moment.

00:23:52.055 --> 00:23:55.891
Like I told you before, you're too quick to jump to conclusions.

00:23:55.892 --> 00:23:59.478
If you're going to use a word like that, you have to have a reason.

00:23:59.479 --> 00:24:00.397
Reason?

00:24:00.981 --> 00:24:03.107
You said those two were dating.

00:24:03.108 --> 00:24:07.111
Yet he smiled to himself when his lover died? It doesn't add up.

00:24:07.112 --> 00:24:08.947
Are you doubting me again?

00:24:09.448 --> 00:24:10.656
I saw it as clear as day!

00:24:10.657 --> 00:24:13.118
No, I'm not doubting you.

00:24:14.035 --> 00:24:18.331
The character and plot lack the plausibility to call it malice.

00:24:18.999 --> 00:24:21.041
First, we need to find out

00:24:21.042 --> 00:24:23.920
What happened between them right before the accident.

00:24:25.380 --> 00:24:26.381
So,

00:24:27.674 --> 00:24:29.009
Are you asking me

00:24:29.968 --> 00:24:31.052
To go to that hotel?

00:24:32.971 --> 00:24:34.097
Now you're getting it.

00:24:36.099 --> 00:24:37.434
Put differently...

00:24:39.936 --> 00:24:40.812
This is

00:24:41.813 --> 00:24:43.231
An investigative assignment.

00:24:44.733 --> 00:24:47.152
By investigating, we'll bring realism to your story.

00:24:51.406 --> 00:24:53.366
Do you know my heart just skipped a beat?

00:24:53.867 --> 00:24:54.826
So you're telling me

00:24:55.327 --> 00:24:59.080
To go there in person and dig into the scene, right?

00:25:00.248 --> 00:25:02.792
- Don't get so worked up. Sit. - Yes, sir.

00:25:03.293 --> 00:25:04.793
Why are you getting so worked up?

00:25:04.794 --> 00:25:07.380
Best to stay calm, especially in situations like this.

00:25:08.173 --> 00:25:10.841
Okay. I have some time tomorrow afternoon.

00:25:10.842 --> 00:25:12.010
All right, then.

00:25:12.719 --> 00:25:13.678
I'll be going.

00:25:15.722 --> 00:25:17.349
Would you like to come with me?

00:25:18.558 --> 00:25:19.392
Me?

00:25:21.019 --> 00:25:22.436
Why would I go there?

00:25:22.437 --> 00:25:23.563
Why not?

00:25:24.439 --> 00:25:25.815
Are you scared of losing face?

00:25:27.567 --> 00:25:30.445
Face? Please. I have important plans tomorrow.

00:25:32.822 --> 00:25:35.158
You punk, do you think I'm lying?

00:25:38.787 --> 00:25:40.288
What are you doing tomorrow?

00:25:47.128 --> 00:25:48.463
If you aren't busy...

00:25:50.590 --> 00:25:54.344
I was thinking we could go out. Watch a movie or something.

00:26:00.934 --> 00:26:02.852
Can't you tell?

00:26:03.687 --> 00:26:04.729
I'm...

00:26:06.815 --> 00:26:08.608
Asking you out on a date.

00:26:48.148 --> 00:26:49.733
<i>Damn it, my car keys.</i>

00:26:50.317 --> 00:26:51.192
<i>My car keys.</i>

00:26:51.860 --> 00:26:53.611
<i>They're not here? Where are they?</i>

00:26:53.612 --> 00:26:56.656
<i>My darn car keys!</i>

00:27:09.002 --> 00:27:11.795
<i>Mr. Heo, I just got back from the hotel.</i>

00:27:11.796 --> 00:27:15.758
<i>If I start on my assignment now, it should be in your inbox in two hours.</i>

00:27:15.759 --> 00:27:17.886
<i>There are so many shocking developments.</i>

00:27:22.849 --> 00:27:24.434
He asked you out on a date?

00:27:25.852 --> 00:27:27.520
Yesterday, out of the blue.

00:27:28.313 --> 00:27:31.358
He asked to go to the movies alone, but that would be no fun.

00:27:32.025 --> 00:27:33.610
So I asked you to join us.

00:27:35.820 --> 00:27:38.280
Or maybe you invited us to brag about your date.

00:27:38.281 --> 00:27:39.741
Brag? Oh, please.

00:27:42.369 --> 00:27:43.787
You're so cheeky.

00:27:44.287 --> 00:27:46.372
Can't you just turn a blind eye for once?

00:27:46.373 --> 00:27:49.583
You're not the only couple that goes on dates.

00:27:49.584 --> 00:27:50.919
Right, honey?

00:27:56.383 --> 00:27:58.176
What are you doing? Answer me.

00:27:59.344 --> 00:28:00.345
Answer what?

00:28:04.849 --> 00:28:05.974
He's been weird lately...

00:28:05.975 --> 00:28:08.103
<i>It's been two hours. Where's your assignment?</i>

00:28:09.104 --> 00:28:11.106
He's acting out of character? How?

00:28:12.982 --> 00:28:14.734
He sleeps in my room sometimes.

00:28:16.236 --> 00:28:17.070
Oh my!

00:28:17.654 --> 00:28:21.157
Wow, Mun-oh. That's great! Wow.

00:28:25.036 --> 00:28:26.620
No, this is a good thing.

00:28:26.621 --> 00:28:30.499
That explains why you've been glowing these days, Hyeon-suk.

00:28:30.500 --> 00:28:31.418
Excuse me?

00:28:32.043 --> 00:28:34.545
What are you talking about? I always glow.

00:28:34.546 --> 00:28:37.090
- You have always been beautiful. - Yeah.

00:28:37.590 --> 00:28:38.633
Mun-oh.

00:28:39.134 --> 00:28:43.680
Please, just be good to Hyeon-suk. Don't leave her lonely like back then.

00:28:44.180 --> 00:28:45.807
Hey, back then?

00:28:46.307 --> 00:28:47.434
Yeah, in the past.

00:28:48.226 --> 00:28:50.603
When you had multiple miscarriages.

00:28:51.104 --> 00:28:52.814
And when you were trying IVF.

00:28:54.315 --> 00:28:56.734
Why are you bringing that up right now?

00:28:56.735 --> 00:28:58.695
Mun-oh was so inattentive then.

00:29:00.280 --> 00:29:01.822
Do you even know

00:29:01.823 --> 00:29:04.575
How lonely she was and how much she suffered back then?

00:29:04.576 --> 00:29:06.952
Come on, honey. What's with you?

00:29:06.953 --> 00:29:08.663
What, am I wrong?

00:29:09.748 --> 00:29:11.207
That's how you were.

00:29:11.833 --> 00:29:12.833
You were exhausted...

00:29:12.834 --> 00:29:16.086
<i>I just sent you my assignment. Sorry for the delay, Mr. Heo.</i>

00:29:16.087 --> 00:29:20.133
...yet you were more worried about Mun-oh's creative slump or whatever than yourself.

00:29:20.759 --> 00:29:22.509
I'm going to go to the restroom.

00:29:22.510 --> 00:29:24.220
Yes, go ahead.

00:29:29.058 --> 00:29:30.769
I hate to tell you "I told you so,"

00:29:31.269 --> 00:29:34.146
But you were so head over heels for a writer.

00:29:34.147 --> 00:29:35.063
Hey!

00:29:35.064 --> 00:29:39.277
He left because he's embarrassed. How could you say that to his face?

00:29:39.903 --> 00:29:42.530
That was then. He's good to me now!

00:30:07.555 --> 00:30:08.598
<i>By then,</i>

00:30:09.182 --> 00:30:11.392
<i>the bloodstains had been wiped away completely.</i>

00:30:32.789 --> 00:30:34.040
I'm not sure.

00:30:34.541 --> 00:30:36.668
I can't remember every single guest.

00:30:37.168 --> 00:30:40.671
And even if I did, I can't just give out our guests' personal information.

00:30:40.672 --> 00:30:43.424
And the car accident has nothing to do with our hotel.

00:30:44.092 --> 00:30:46.511
If I may, why do you ask?

00:30:47.053 --> 00:30:48.304
What's this about?

00:30:48.805 --> 00:30:50.348
I see. Thank you.

00:31:09.450 --> 00:31:11.202
- Excuse me. - Yes?

00:31:12.579 --> 00:31:14.121
- One moment, please. - Yes?

00:31:14.122 --> 00:31:17.333
Have you seen this man among the guests?

00:31:17.876 --> 00:31:19.043
No, I haven't.

00:31:21.337 --> 00:31:22.964
Do you recognize this man?

00:31:24.465 --> 00:31:26.050
I've never seen him before.

00:31:29.888 --> 00:31:31.097
I don't know him.

00:31:35.977 --> 00:31:37.270
I'm not sure.

00:31:44.152 --> 00:31:45.778
Whoa, sorry.

00:31:46.446 --> 00:31:47.447
Apologies.

00:31:48.114 --> 00:31:50.658
You're not allowed in here.

00:31:53.036 --> 00:31:55.288
Sir? The exit is this way.

00:31:56.372 --> 00:31:57.373
I know that.

00:32:01.419 --> 00:32:02.253
Lee Kang?

00:32:05.340 --> 00:32:07.133
Is that you? Lee Kang?

00:32:08.801 --> 00:32:09.636
Jae-sik?

00:32:12.263 --> 00:32:13.305
Jae-sik!

00:32:13.306 --> 00:32:15.057
<i>It was an incredible stroke of luck.</i>

00:32:15.058 --> 00:32:16.016
How've you been?

00:32:16.017 --> 00:32:18.144
<i>Had I not met Jae-sik at that moment,</i>

00:32:18.728 --> 00:32:21.648
<i>the truth would have stayed buried in the dark forever.</i>

00:32:28.446 --> 00:32:29.572
<i>I first met Jae-sik</i>

00:32:30.573 --> 00:32:31.991
<i>last summer.</i>

00:32:37.497 --> 00:32:38.915
"Lee Kang."

00:32:39.791 --> 00:32:40.750
High school senior?

00:32:43.711 --> 00:32:46.756
Don't seniors usually spend the summer studying at the academy?

00:32:47.632 --> 00:32:49.676
Yet you're wasting your precious time working.

00:32:50.176 --> 00:32:51.678
What a tough life.

00:32:57.433 --> 00:32:59.185
What are you studying?

00:33:02.355 --> 00:33:03.564
The civil servant exam?

00:33:05.066 --> 00:33:06.067
"Oh Jae-sik."

00:33:06.859 --> 00:33:08.111
I'm just getting started.

00:33:09.988 --> 00:33:12.573
Actually, it's my third attempt at starting. Fuck my life.

00:33:17.662 --> 00:33:20.164
<i>Holy crap, Yeonseo University? Brainy bastard, huh?</i>

00:33:23.126 --> 00:33:24.961
What about you? The civil servant exam.

00:33:26.379 --> 00:33:27.213
Not yet.

00:33:28.089 --> 00:33:29.841
I'm not giving up. Don't write me off.

00:33:30.591 --> 00:33:33.344
Write you off? Never. You're cool just as you are.

00:33:35.221 --> 00:33:36.055
Really?

00:33:37.265 --> 00:33:40.309
I mean, yeah. Working at the hotel isn't so bad.

00:33:42.020 --> 00:33:44.981
What about that car accident? What do you want to know?

00:33:45.481 --> 00:33:47.608
Well, it's a long story.

00:33:48.276 --> 00:33:51.487
It's strictly personal. I kind of knew the woman who died.

00:33:52.405 --> 00:33:54.157
Is that right?

00:33:54.657 --> 00:33:55.700
You knew her?

00:33:56.284 --> 00:33:58.077
Yeah, I just feel bad for her.

00:33:58.911 --> 00:34:01.873
I'd like to know what happened before the accident,

00:34:03.499 --> 00:34:05.084
But no one will tell me shit.

00:34:07.712 --> 00:34:08.713
I bet no one else...

00:34:10.423 --> 00:34:12.091
Knows more about it than I do.

00:34:14.427 --> 00:34:15.261
Really?

00:34:17.555 --> 00:34:18.473
I

00:34:19.974 --> 00:34:21.559
Even witnessed the accident.

00:34:23.436 --> 00:34:25.730
<i>I was on my way home from work.</i>

00:34:27.565 --> 00:34:29.358
Talk to me before you go!

00:34:30.151 --> 00:34:30.984
I'm not talking...

00:34:30.985 --> 00:34:34.738
<i>I recognized them right away.</i>

00:34:34.739 --> 00:34:35.822
<i>Especially...</i>

00:34:35.823 --> 00:34:36.740
Min-hui!

00:34:36.741 --> 00:34:37.825
<i>...that man.</i>

00:34:38.910 --> 00:34:40.620
What? You scared?

00:34:41.412 --> 00:34:44.040
Just wait and see the shit I pull.

00:34:52.507 --> 00:34:54.216
- Call an ambulance. - Holy crap.

00:34:54.217 --> 00:34:56.384
- What the... - Someone call an ambulance!

00:34:56.385 --> 00:34:57.928
- We need an ambulance. - My God!

00:34:57.929 --> 00:34:59.888
- A car accident. - She came out of nowhere!

00:34:59.889 --> 00:35:01.641
Yeah, all of a sudden.

00:35:05.394 --> 00:35:06.479
That man.

00:35:07.146 --> 00:35:07.980
Who was he?

00:35:09.107 --> 00:35:10.149
That man

00:35:10.775 --> 00:35:13.319
<i>was a regular at our suite.</i>

00:35:15.154 --> 00:35:17.657
"A regular at the hotel suite"?

00:35:20.535 --> 00:35:21.661
Kim Su-hun was?

00:35:24.330 --> 00:35:26.290
<i>He came three or four times a month</i>

00:35:27.041 --> 00:35:29.000
<i>and always reserved</i> that <i>room.</i>

00:35:29.001 --> 00:35:31.003
<i>But the funny thing is,</i>

00:35:31.587 --> 00:35:33.588
<i>he would always order top-shelf wine</i>

00:35:33.589 --> 00:35:36.049
<i>with a side of cheap ice cream through room service.</i>

00:35:36.050 --> 00:35:39.386
<i>Wait, cheap ice cream? Why?</i>

00:35:39.387 --> 00:35:42.765
<i>I wouldn't know. I guess that's up to our imaginations.</i>

00:35:45.977 --> 00:35:48.271
Hello, sir. Room service.

00:35:50.481 --> 00:35:51.732
Thank you, sir.

00:35:55.486 --> 00:35:57.572
<i>The woman's outfit changed every time.</i>

00:35:58.072 --> 00:36:01.617
<i>A nurse costume one day. A bunny, the next.</i>

00:36:02.118 --> 00:36:04.995
<i>And another day, a schoolgirl uniform.</i>

00:36:04.996 --> 00:36:06.330
Yeah, Mr. Choi.

00:36:07.415 --> 00:36:08.499
Not at all.

00:36:09.458 --> 00:36:10.877
I'm on a trip.

00:36:12.211 --> 00:36:14.547
No, just me without my wife.

00:36:15.548 --> 00:36:17.049
No, I'm not writing.

00:36:17.884 --> 00:36:19.343
I don't have anything written.

00:36:20.094 --> 00:36:23.097
<i>- The truth is, he's an author.</i> - Just needed some inspiration.

00:36:23.890 --> 00:36:26.142
<i>He probably thought someone like me wouldn't know.</i>

00:36:27.351 --> 00:36:28.477
<i>He's an author?</i>

00:36:29.103 --> 00:36:30.313
Yeah.

00:36:43.201 --> 00:36:44.952
Man, how could an author...

00:36:45.661 --> 00:36:47.079
And he's married, you say?

00:36:48.289 --> 00:36:50.165
Bastards like him are the worst.

00:36:50.166 --> 00:36:53.085
They act respectable in public but are sick pervs in private.

00:36:54.295 --> 00:36:58.382
So that's what he was doing that day too? The day of the accident?

00:36:58.883 --> 00:36:59.800
No.

00:37:00.301 --> 00:37:01.344
That day was

00:37:02.178 --> 00:37:03.387
A little different.

00:37:03.971 --> 00:37:05.556
A bit unusual, you could say.

00:37:06.724 --> 00:37:07.934
Unusual?

00:37:08.434 --> 00:37:11.979
Yeah. The noises I heard that day were a little different.

00:37:12.855 --> 00:37:14.815
I didn't mean to eavesdrop, but...

00:37:17.193 --> 00:37:18.527
What different noises?

00:37:20.154 --> 00:37:20.988
Well, you see...

00:37:24.033 --> 00:37:25.159
WIFE

00:37:30.581 --> 00:37:33.584
What I heard was...

00:37:34.877 --> 00:37:35.710
PARK HYEONG-JONG

00:37:35.711 --> 00:37:38.047
Why are you people doing this?

00:37:41.842 --> 00:37:43.134
Professor Park, what is it?

00:37:43.135 --> 00:37:45.012
<i>Mun-oh, where are you?</i>

00:37:45.513 --> 00:37:47.138
<i>Come on, why aren't you back yet?</i>

00:37:47.139 --> 00:37:49.891
I'll be back soon. What is it?

00:37:49.892 --> 00:37:52.812
<i>Mun-oh, guess who is here with us right now?</i>

00:37:53.312 --> 00:37:55.189
<i>Do you know who we just bumped into?</i>

00:37:55.940 --> 00:37:57.733
What are you talking about?

00:38:03.656 --> 00:38:04.657
Wait, who?

00:38:08.953 --> 00:38:10.621
Let's get one altogether.

00:38:11.163 --> 00:38:13.123
Three, two, one.

00:38:13.124 --> 00:38:14.041
There you are.

00:38:14.542 --> 00:38:15.751
Hey, Mun-oh.

00:38:16.752 --> 00:38:18.921
Fancy seeing you here, huh?

00:38:19.755 --> 00:38:20.798
How have you been?

00:38:21.590 --> 00:38:22.424
Why are you here?

00:38:22.425 --> 00:38:24.010
A surprise, isn't it?

00:38:24.510 --> 00:38:28.305
I spotted him on his way home from a meeting with a publishing house

00:38:28.306 --> 00:38:30.307
And asked him to join.

00:38:30.308 --> 00:38:31.809
A publishing house?

00:38:33.311 --> 00:38:36.813
What took you so long in the restroom? What were you doing?

00:38:36.814 --> 00:38:38.816
You didn't even answer my call.

00:38:39.900 --> 00:38:41.192
It wasn't that long.

00:38:41.193 --> 00:38:44.321
Anyway, I hope I'm not interrupting your fun.

00:38:44.322 --> 00:38:45.238
Not at all.

00:38:45.239 --> 00:38:48.742
You're not interrupting at all. I'm so excited right now.

00:38:48.743 --> 00:38:50.994
Meeting you has been the highlight of the day.

00:38:50.995 --> 00:38:51.953
Absolutely.

00:38:51.954 --> 00:38:54.957
It's always an honor to be in your company.

00:38:55.458 --> 00:38:59.377
He's talked about you a lot since that lecture.

00:38:59.378 --> 00:39:04.133
He's been bragging to everyone about the pleasure of meeting you.

00:39:05.301 --> 00:39:06.635
I see.

00:39:07.345 --> 00:39:10.097
This is the first I've heard about the lecture.

00:39:12.016 --> 00:39:15.269
That's how this one is. Always so reserved.

00:39:15.770 --> 00:39:18.731
I didn't even know that you two were in college together.

00:39:19.231 --> 00:39:22.443
Is that right? Eun-joo and I talked about you from time to time.

00:39:24.320 --> 00:39:25.446
Eun-joo?

00:39:26.530 --> 00:39:29.241
My wife went to the same school. She's Mun-oh's junior.

00:39:34.747 --> 00:39:36.540
You two talked about me?

00:39:40.878 --> 00:39:42.754
And how is Eun-joo?

00:39:42.755 --> 00:39:44.631
Yeah, she's doing well.

00:39:44.632 --> 00:39:47.384
Actually, my second kid is attending Yeonseo University.

00:39:47.385 --> 00:39:51.389
Turns out he's in your class. So we talked about you sometimes.

00:39:53.599 --> 00:39:54.600
I see.

00:39:55.351 --> 00:39:56.685
That's news to me.

00:39:58.687 --> 00:40:01.941
What was he like back in university?

00:40:05.403 --> 00:40:07.363
Well, he was pretty reserved.

00:40:08.030 --> 00:40:12.117
Always sitting in the last row of the lecture hall, like an observer.

00:40:12.118 --> 00:40:14.412
It was rather cunning.

00:40:14.954 --> 00:40:16.454
But that's also Mun-oh's charm.

00:40:16.455 --> 00:40:18.416
So you haven't changed a bit.

00:40:22.711 --> 00:40:26.048
And why did you meet with the president of that publishing house?

00:40:26.924 --> 00:40:28.216
To discuss your next book?

00:40:28.217 --> 00:40:32.178
Not my next book. He's already talking about the one that'll come after.

00:40:32.179 --> 00:40:35.057
But I need ideas for my next book or the one after that.

00:40:35.975 --> 00:40:36.892
Speaking of,

00:40:37.893 --> 00:40:41.021
Where <i>do</i> you usually get your ideas from?

00:40:43.816 --> 00:40:46.235
Where do you find new inspiration?

00:40:47.820 --> 00:40:49.071
Well, that's...

00:40:50.698 --> 00:40:53.284
What? Is it awkward to share?

00:40:54.910 --> 00:40:56.745
I'm just curious.

00:40:59.582 --> 00:41:01.041
Perhaps you

00:41:02.460 --> 00:41:05.671
Travel to new places

00:41:06.589 --> 00:41:07.506
Or...

00:41:10.509 --> 00:41:11.885
Meet someone new

00:41:11.886 --> 00:41:14.555
And experience a thrilling deviation from everyday life.

00:41:18.642 --> 00:41:21.020
I wouldn't call it a deviation from my everyday life,

00:41:22.563 --> 00:41:25.232
But I do travel a lot. Why do you ask?

00:41:28.027 --> 00:41:29.111
The truth is,

00:41:29.653 --> 00:41:33.365
He's asking because he's genuinely curious.

00:41:34.241 --> 00:41:37.495
He's been in a slump for a long time since writing his first novel.

00:41:38.120 --> 00:41:39.537
So he's just curious

00:41:39.538 --> 00:41:42.041
How you do it.

00:41:43.292 --> 00:41:44.126
Is that so?

00:41:46.879 --> 00:41:48.214
<i>Why the hell?</i>

00:41:48.797 --> 00:41:50.131
Why the hell?

00:41:50.132 --> 00:41:51.883
Why did you say that crap, huh?

00:41:51.884 --> 00:41:56.012
Why would you say that crap about me being in a slump in front of that bastard?

00:41:56.013 --> 00:41:58.056
And why didn't you tell me?

00:41:58.057 --> 00:42:00.808
Why did you hide the fact that you went to school with him?

00:42:00.809 --> 00:42:01.726
What?

00:42:01.727 --> 00:42:05.188
Did you not want to even say his name after he stole the girl you liked?

00:42:05.189 --> 00:42:07.775
- What did you say? - That's her name, isn't it?

00:42:08.442 --> 00:42:10.611
Ahn Eun-joo, Kim Su-hun's wife!

00:42:11.445 --> 00:42:13.780
Who is she? Who even is she to you?

00:42:13.781 --> 00:42:16.991
You said it was all in the past. What, still got feelings for her?

00:42:16.992 --> 00:42:19.702
Why do you keep hiding things from me? I hate that!

00:42:19.703 --> 00:42:21.705
Hiding what? It's not like that.

00:42:22.957 --> 00:42:25.584
Or do you really have an inferiority complex toward him?

00:42:26.585 --> 00:42:28.002
Is that why you didn't tell me?

00:42:28.003 --> 00:42:29.838
Are you done?

00:42:32.424 --> 00:42:35.970
Do you know what a son of a bitch that bastard Kim Su-hun is?

00:42:43.852 --> 00:42:46.855
How am I supposed to know if you don't tell me?

00:43:22.182 --> 00:43:24.143
<i>It was an unusual day.</i>

00:43:24.643 --> 00:43:27.228
<i>The noises I heard that day were a little different.</i>

00:43:27.229 --> 00:43:29.940
<i>How? What different noises?</i>

00:43:31.442 --> 00:43:32.942
- Let go! - Cut it out!

00:43:32.943 --> 00:43:35.194
Should I call your family? Want me to call?

00:43:35.195 --> 00:43:38.406
Are you threatening me? Keep testing me like this, and you'll pay!

00:43:38.407 --> 00:43:42.077
What? I'll pay? And how exactly will you make me pay?

00:43:42.578 --> 00:43:44.537
Fine, you son of a bitch!

00:43:44.538 --> 00:43:46.164
Do whatever you want!

00:43:46.165 --> 00:43:48.708
I'll expose you for who you really are!

00:43:48.709 --> 00:43:49.959
I even have proof!

00:43:49.960 --> 00:43:52.378
<i>- So they were fighting? -</i> I have proof right here!

00:43:52.379 --> 00:43:55.257
No, not so much fighting.

00:43:55.758 --> 00:43:58.469
More like hurling threats at each other.

00:43:58.969 --> 00:43:59.970
Threats?

00:44:01.430 --> 00:44:04.642
And what was it like when you went into the room?

00:44:05.726 --> 00:44:07.978
He told me to leave the tray by the door that day.

00:44:10.564 --> 00:44:12.399
I wonder what threats she made.

00:44:13.359 --> 00:44:15.277
And what was the proof she mentioned?

00:44:16.820 --> 00:44:19.447
Hello? Yes, I'll head back right away.

00:44:19.448 --> 00:44:20.532
Okay.

00:44:22.743 --> 00:44:24.703
- I should get back. - Sure, Jae-sik.

00:44:25.412 --> 00:44:28.916
- Sorry I kept you for so long. - No, this was fun. It was nice seeing you.

00:44:29.416 --> 00:44:30.541
- See you soon. - Yeah.

00:44:30.542 --> 00:44:32.835
Come visit me. I'll be here, okay?

00:44:32.836 --> 00:44:33.879
See you.

00:44:36.340 --> 00:44:37.508
Right, yesterday.

00:44:38.300 --> 00:44:40.803
A guy about your age came to the hotel yesterday.

00:44:41.345 --> 00:44:42.178
What?

00:44:42.179 --> 00:44:45.557
He asked if anything had happened before the accident. Just like you.

00:44:48.644 --> 00:44:49.603
Really?

00:44:50.437 --> 00:44:51.271
Who was he?

00:44:52.106 --> 00:44:52.940
I don't know.

00:44:53.440 --> 00:44:56.193
But he asked me something strange at the end.

00:44:57.903 --> 00:44:59.697
If it was really a car accident,

00:45:01.031 --> 00:45:03.033
Or if it could have been a murder.

00:45:04.535 --> 00:45:06.120
- A murder? - Yeah.

00:45:06.787 --> 00:45:08.579
It threw me off at first too.

00:45:08.580 --> 00:45:10.833
I witnessed the accident myself, after all.

00:45:11.542 --> 00:45:16.797
But I thought hard about it after he left, and something felt off.

00:45:17.965 --> 00:45:18.965
Don't you think?

00:45:18.966 --> 00:45:21.301
He wouldn't have known the two of them fought.

00:45:21.885 --> 00:45:23.387
I didn't tell him either.

00:45:24.138 --> 00:45:27.933
So why did he suddenly bring up the possibility of murder?

00:45:28.809 --> 00:45:30.018
What does he know?

00:45:30.769 --> 00:45:32.020
What does he suspect?

00:45:40.738 --> 00:45:41.905
Murder?

00:46:04.636 --> 00:46:07.097
Did you think this would be enough to get rid of me?

00:46:08.599 --> 00:46:10.309
You crazy bitch!

00:46:20.068 --> 00:46:21.444
- Let go! - Cut it out!

00:46:21.445 --> 00:46:23.696
Should I call your family? Want me to call?

00:46:23.697 --> 00:46:27.033
Are you threatening me? Keep testing me like this, and you'll pay!

00:46:27.034 --> 00:46:30.621
What? I'll pay? And how exactly will you make me pay?

00:46:31.121 --> 00:46:33.080
Fine, you son of a bitch!

00:46:33.081 --> 00:46:34.499
Do whatever you want!

00:46:34.500 --> 00:46:37.001
I'll expose you for who you really are!

00:46:37.002 --> 00:46:39.671
I even have proof! I have proof right--

00:47:37.896 --> 00:47:39.273
Kim Su-hun.

00:47:41.942 --> 00:47:43.569
What have you...

00:47:45.821 --> 00:47:47.531
What did you do?

00:47:49.908 --> 00:47:51.785
What have you done?

00:48:00.836 --> 00:48:01.753
Hurry.

00:48:07.259 --> 00:48:08.093
Hey, Lee Kang!

00:48:08.844 --> 00:48:10.637
Find that young man.

00:48:11.263 --> 00:48:13.432
<i>Mr. Heo? What time is--</i>

00:48:14.266 --> 00:48:16.893
No, we need to know who that guy is!

00:48:16.894 --> 00:48:19.688
The young man who brought up the possibility of murder.

00:48:20.689 --> 00:48:23.400
Go back to the hotel tomorrow and try to find out who he is.

00:48:23.901 --> 00:48:27.154
Check all the security footage if you have to. Then we're good.

00:48:28.822 --> 00:48:31.408
Then we'll know what that proof is.

00:48:31.909 --> 00:48:34.036
<i>Mr. Heo, please calm down.</i>

00:48:34.786 --> 00:48:36.955
You <i>told me not to get all worked up, remember?</i>

00:48:37.539 --> 00:48:41.126
<i>I was going to tell you tomorrow anyway...</i>

00:48:43.253 --> 00:48:45.213
<i>but I think I know who he is.</i>

00:48:45.964 --> 00:48:46.924
What did you say?

00:50:20.225 --> 00:50:21.059
Sis?

00:50:27.149 --> 00:50:28.233
Dad...

00:50:33.405 --> 00:50:34.948
Killed someone.

00:50:44.374 --> 00:50:45.667
I said Dad...

00:50:50.797 --> 00:50:52.466
Killed someone.

00:51:01.767 --> 00:51:04.770
NOTES FROM THE LAST ROW

00:53:30.874 --> 00:53:35.879
Subtitle translation by: Jimin Choi

